Drivers who can relapse due to alcohol levels will have to install the ‘alcolock’.
The authority orders that the driver, who had three official penalties for the alcohol level, install in his car this system, which prohibits him from starting the car in the drunk state.
The initiative was announced last month in June and is already part of the report of the Attorney General. According to their data, this is a pilot project that will last for a year.
The purpose is to rehabilitate the driver, which is why he gets a course for re-educating traffic behavior.
