Talking in sleep
Some children talk at night
I don’t mean those who wake up and tell us something that happened the day before, but the children who talk during sleep.
When it happens to you for the first time, at best you will be frightened, but in reality it doesn’t matter.
This is a positive sleep disorder called speaking during sleep.
It is quite common, especially among children and adolescents.
Certainly, more than one of you was told that you were talking at night.
This phenomenon can occur occasionally (once in life, for example, during high fever), or regularly (every day, once a week, once a month), the next day the child can remember nothing.
There is not a single reason that causes this phenomenon.
Often, relationships are sought with other phenomena in sleep, such as nightmares, panic at night, Enuresis noctura (bedwetting at night), speaking in sleep, but there is no reason for this.
As we mentioned earlier, it can be due to very high fiber, stressful situations or overload.
In any case, this is a little researched phenomenon.
The frequency with which it occurs is very variable.
It may be that you speak quietly in individual words, whisper or it may be quite an opposite (screaming, crying, long discussions).
In cases where the utterance is very intense, it is recommended to observe the child and get advice from a specialist to check if there is a problem that causes anxiety and comes about in this way.
We have said that it is a positive disorder, so it is not treated, whether it is associated with another sleep disorder that can be treated (for example, with sleep apnea or with stress).
